# Windsor Terraform Style

- Use underscore-only resource names; never use hyphens in Terraform identifiers.
- Keep modules small and focused by system layer and implementation (`terraform/<layer>/<impl>`).
- Avoid submodules unless resources are reused within the same parent module.
- Never use third-party modules.
- Prefer explicit variable passing between modules; avoid `terraform_remote_state`.
- Avoid data sources for implicit cross-resource wiring when explicit references or variables are possible.
- Parameterize user inputs with typed variables; do not hardcode provider/business values.
- Mark secret-like inputs/outputs as `sensitive = true`.
- Use concise section headers in `main.tf`:
  - `Provider Configuration`
  - Logical resource groups (for example `Project Resources`, `Domain Resources`, `Environment Variable Resources`)
- Keep inline comments out of resource blocks; use block-level comments before resources when needed.
- Use locals for repeated or complex expressions.
- Use `depends_on` only for non-inferable dependencies.
- Require standard module files:
  - `main.tf`
  - `variables.tf`
  - `outputs.tf`
  - `test.tftest.hcl`
  - `README.md`
